ent the established method for quantifying the yield from\nthe optical-element aFWM process based on the beam cross-section dependence.\nWith the new method, the number of signal photons was found to be consistent\nwith zero. We then successfully obtained a new exclusion region in the relation\nbetween ALP-photon coupling, $g/M$, and the ALP mass $m$, reaching the most\nsensitive point $g/M = 1.14\\times10^{-5}\\,\\mathrm{GeV^{-1}}$ at $m =\n0.18\\,\\mathrm{eV}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Aug 2022 13:21:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-23"}
